    <stitle>No Idle APU/HVAC System - MAINTENANCE - Checking / Adjusting Water Pump Belt Tension</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Checking / Adjusting Water Pump Belt Tension</title>
        <para>To check water pump belt tension, proceed as follows:</para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Measure the deflection, depressing the belt halfway between the fan drive pulley and the belt
                    tensioner pulley at 98N (10kgf, 22lbs) of force.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>If the measurement is not the specified value, loosen the bolts and the nuts and relocate the belt
                    tensioner to adjust.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <figure id="f1603718" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603718.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 18. Checking/Adjusting Water Pump Belt Tension</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>To adjust water pump belt tension, proceed as follows:</para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Loosen tensioner nut using a 14mm wrench.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Tap the outside of the tensioner pulley using a rubber mallet to ensure proper spring tension.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Tighten tensioner nut using 14mm wrench.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
